    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>130700</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#_χ_"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><seg part="M">χ</seg><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></name></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><w lemma="δεκάτα"><supplied reason="lost">δ</supplied>εκά<supplied reason="lost">ταν</supplied></w> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>kh<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="subaudible">a consacré ce monument</supplied> au titre de la dîme.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ch<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicated this monument</supplied> as a tithe.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ch<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="subaudible">ha dedicato questo monumento</supplied> come decima.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>The small vestige of line 2 is sufficient to show that we have here a tithe. The larger xhi of line 1, as it cannot belong to the name of Apollo, is certainly
                   part of the dedicant's mention, namely of his father's name, whereas his own name, wholly lost, would have stood at the preceding line.</p>
	           <p>At  line 2, given the smaller lettering, another word should have stood after <foreign xml:lang="grc">δεκάτα</foreign>, either the verb 'dedicated' or 
	           the name of Apollo.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
